& [DeepResearchUnit] is complete
  + [lane] is Hodge Conjecture
  + [low_resolution_signal] is algebraic correspondence generation from arbitrary rational Hodge classes
  + [bounded_question] is whether known Hodge, standard-conjecture, normal-function, absolute-Hodge, or motivated-cycle machinery supplies a theorem that generates algebraic correspondences from arbitrary Hodge-class input
  + [curiosity_priority] is high
    = reason: correspondence generation is the closest proof-shaped bridge from scoped transfer to arbitrary cycle output

& [SourceSet] is the bounded research surface
  + [source_001] is Clay Mathematics Institute Hodge problem statement
    = link: https://www.claymath.org/wp-content/uploads/2022/06/hodge.pdf
    = use: preserves the target as rational Hodge classes being rational combinations of algebraic cycle classes
  + [source_002] is Arapura and Kang, Known cases of the Hodge conjecture
    = link: https://ar5iv.labs.arxiv.org/html/2105.04695
    = use: surveys known cases and the Griffiths-Green approach, emphasizing scoped successes rather than arbitrary correspondence generation
  + [source_003] is Voisin, The Hodge conjecture
    = link: https://webusers.imj-prg.fr/~claire.voisin/Articlesweb/voisinhodge.pdf
    = use: frames Hodge as relation between topological/Hodge data and algebraic cycles, not as an available construction algorithm
  + [source_004] is Griffiths, Hodge theory and geometry
    = link: https://publications.ias.edu/sites/default/files/hodgegeom.pdf
    = use: emphasizes the continuing difficulty of constructing geometric objects such as algebraic cycles beyond classical cases
  + [source_005] is Charles and Schnell, Notes on absolute Hodge classes
    = link: https://www.math.ens.psl.eu/~charles/AH.pdf
    = use: absolute Hodge classes sit between Hodge classes and algebraic cycles, but are not known in general to be algebraic
  + [source_006] is Voisin, Hodge loci and absolute Hodge classes
    = link: https://webusers.imj-prg.fr/~claire.voisin/Articlesweb/com143.4%20945-958.pdf
    = use: Hodge-locus definability gives powerful geometry under hypotheses, but does not provide arbitrary cycle output
  + [source_007] is MathOverflow discussion on standard, Hodge, and Tate conjectures
    = link: https://mathoverflow.net/questions/177366/connections-between-standard-hodge-and-tate-conjectures-on-algebraic-cycles
    = use: standard conjectures are correspondence-rich but remain conjectural and not a general generation theorem from arbitrary Hodge classes

& [ResearchFindings] is the theorem-boundary result
  + [finding_001] is correspondence frameworks are central but not generative enough
    = meaning: standard conjectures and motives organize algebraic correspondences, but do not supply arbitrary Hodge-class-to-correspondence construction in the admitted record
  + [finding_002] is absolute and motivated classes are substitute or intermediate structures
    = meaning: they are useful periphery, but do not equal algebraic cycle output for the Clay target
  + [finding_003] is Hodge loci and normal functions organize detection and variation
    = meaning: they help locate or constrain Hodge classes, but do not output arbitrary algebraic cycles
  + [finding_004] is known cases remain scoped
    = meaning: special varieties, families, and low-codimension cases calibrate proof shape but do not transfer universally
  + [finding_005] is no correspondence-generation theorem was found
    = meaning: the active Hodge reentry remains blocked at arbitrary input to cycle/correspondence output

